Negative questions

We can use negative questions to ask for a confirmation of what we believe to be true or to check information.
To ask a negative question, begin with a negative auxiliary verb.

Haven't you clean it yet?
(I believe it hasn't been cleaned.)

Isn't the movie great?
(Do you agree with me that movie is great.)

Didn't you see her yesterday?
(Confirm that you saw her yesterday.)

Won't you be sad about leaving?
(I believe you'll be sad.)

